This paper proposes a new clustering method that extends an existing method using belief functions. The paper focuses on the application of the method to real clustering problems and presents experimental results. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper deals with clustering, which is a subfield of data mining, so cs.DM (Data Mining) is also a possible sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which makes cs.SI (Systems and Control) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of multiple prototypes, which is a common technique in neural networks, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
